With her white chef's hat, Claudia looks at home in the kitchen of this Berlin restaurant, but her culinary talents are being used to feed people who, like her, suffer from eating disorders.
Hecht says she doesn't talk about her eating disorder with herchildren, but she knows they love her and want her to stop.
This is how Emma, 15, and a fan of Web sites promoting anorexia,nearly starved herself to death: She began by "eating healthy," she says, choosing salads and givingup fast food.
